   GOLF-CLUBS (Carlsbad, Calif.) _ The golf-club business is going
through a serious retrenchment. Despite the sharp rise of interest
in golf from aging baby boomers and a new influx of young people,
sales in the $2.5 billion golf-club market are off 10 to 20 percent
this year. Prices are falling and inventories rising. By Andrew
Pollack and Sharon R. King.
