<P>
   PACIFICARE-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ While the majority of HMOs
are losing money covering the elderly under Medicare, Pacificare,
the nation's largest Medicare HMO, is solidly profitable. And while
managed-care stocks are down by an average of 7 percent so far this
year, Pacificare's nonvoting class B shares are up an impressive 49
percent. But some analysts and investors are not convinced that
Pacificare is quite as exceptional as it may appear. Others believe
it is only a matter of time before the harsh economics facing HMOs
that serve the Medicare population catch up with the company. By
Reed Abelson.
</P>
<P>
   TV-AD-COLUMN _ Network executives are not the only people whose
