wished I could give them both the peace of those few moments, the
sweetness of those sounds, the serenity of that spot. I can't.
 &HT;    But I can remember the true nature of giving, at Christmas and
at every other time. That might be almost as good.
 &HT;     c.1998 Patti Davis  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Patti Davis, a daughter of Ronald Reagan, is an author and
screenwriter.) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   --------------- &QC;
</P>
