   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ The irony of the House impeachment
of President Clinton is that if a presidential election were held
today he would be re-elected. Why have a hefty majority of voters
rallied behind him? By MARIANNE MEANS. (This column was filed
Wednesday.)
