A5823 &Cx1f; tth-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FILM-FACULTY-SPI &LR;      12-24 0399
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-FACULTY-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TEST SCORES ARE MEDIOCRE FOR `THE FACULTY' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By PAULA NECHAK  
 c.1998 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Even though ``The Faculty'' falls apart after its first hour,
for the most part it's moderately entertaining, if reminiscent of
other recent teen sci-fi/horror films such as ``Disturbing
Behavior.''
</P>
<P>
   Robert Rodriguez, director of ``Desperado,'' ``From Dusk Till
Dawn'' and ``El Mariachi,'' works from a script by Kevin
Williamson, the whiz kid responsible for ``Scream'' and ``Scream
2.'' Not surprisingly, ``The Faculty'' is full of the same high
school stereotypes and allusions to movie and TV references.
</P>
<P>
   But ``The Faculty'' isn't as innovative by half as Williamson's
previous blockbusters. Proving that the third time isn't exactly
the charm, the story yanks from ``Alien'' and Jack Finney's
literary science-fiction classic, ``Invasion of the Body
Snatchers.''
</P>
<P>
   Instead of a strange pod that eerily clones its human host into
a zombie, however, ``The Faculty'' introduces an alien sluglike
parasite that gruesomely attaches itself in its victim's ear.
</P>
<P>
   Rundown Herrington High's burned out, second-rate faculty _
including Principal Drake (Bebe Neuwirth), shy Miss Burke (Famke
Janssen) and Coach Willis (Robert Patrick) suddenly take a new
interest in ``teaching.''
</P>
<P>
   That forces a cross-section of kids _ school nerd Casey (Elijah
Wood), football hero Stan (Shawn Hatosy), popular Delilah (Jordana
Brewster), new girl (Laura Harris), drug supplier Zeke (Josh
Hartnett) and punk misfit Stokely (Clea DuVall) _ to endeavor to
find the alien queen.
</P>
<P>
   When they discover their teachers are truly from another planet,
it's up to them to keep the school _ and town _ from turning into a
different kind of student body.
</P>
<P>
   Unfortunately, Rodriguez's direction feels lackluster and
uninspired and doesn't bring anything truly exciting to the table.
</P>
<P>
   Graded on the horror curve, ``The Faculty'' is short on scares
and rates only average marks for such a blatant, if occasionally
amusing, Cliff's Notes version of better, more inspired B-movies.
</P>
<P>
   The Faculty. Directed by Robert Rodriguez. Written by Kevin
Williamson. Cast: Elijah Wood, Famke Janssen, Robert Patrick, Salma
Hayek, Piper Laurie, Bebe Neuwirth. Dimension Films. 102 minutes.
Rated R for violence, language.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: C
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-24-98 1445EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19981224.0122 </DOCNO>
