<P>
   Weekend Section stories from The New York Times News Service for
Friday, Dec. 25.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FEATURES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GREEN-COMDEN (New York) _ An excursion with Adolph Green and
Betty Comden, the longest-running partnership the musical theater
has produced. The two have been professional but not personal
partners since 1938. By Peter Applebome.
</P>
<P>
   NY-STAINED-GLASS (New York) _ A new stained glass window is
unveiled at the Marble Collegiate Church in Manhattan. ``Like
painting in the air with colored light,'' said the donor of the
window, Robert Ryneveld. But there is much newly brilliant glass to
admire around the city. Restoration projects have reclaimed dozens
of darkened and damaged windows by masters like Tiffany, at
Congregation Shearith Israel on the Upper West Side; John La Farge,
at Judson Memorial Church in Greenwich Village, and William Jay
Bolton, at the Church of St. Ann and the Holy Trinity in Brooklyn
Heights. By David W. Dunlap.
</P>
<P>
   FAITH-RESTORED (New York) _ A writer makes a pilgrimage back to
a black church in Brooklyn that inspired his own return to the
Judaism of his ancestors. The Sunday prayer service he attends,
with two spiritual fathers _ a rabbi and a minister _ evokes the
meaning of spirituality that transcends all faiths at this season.
By Samuel G. Freedman.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MOVIES &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CIVIL-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``A Civil Action'':Steven
Zaillian, director; with John Travolta, Robert Duvall, Stephen Fry,
James Gandolfini, Dan Hadaya, William H. Macy, Kathleen Quinlan,
Tony Shalhoub. Reviewed by Janet Maslin.
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Down in the Delta'': Maya
Angelou, director; with Alfre Woodard, Mopho Koaho, Kulani Hassen,
Al Freeman, Jr., Esther Rolle, Loretta Devine, Wesly Snipes.
Reviewed by Stephen Holden.
</P>
<P>
   FACULTY-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``The Faculty'': Robert
Rodriquez, director; with Kevin Williamson, scriptwriter, Robert
Patrick, ElijahWood, Clea Duvall, Shawn Hatosy. Reviewed by
Lawrence Van Gelder.
</P>
<P>
   MIGHTY-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Mighty Joe Young'': Ron
Underwood, director; with Bill Paxton, Charlize Theron. Reviewed by
Stephen Holden.
</P>
<P>
   FILMS4KIDS (Undated) _ Assessing the current cinema for children
of different ages.
</P>
<P>
   AT-THE-MOVIES (Hollywood) _ News of the silver screen. By
Bernard Weinraub.
</P>
