<P>
   HUNTING-HIGHWAY _ It's one of the few really cold mornings of
the hunting season and Mike Ivie, face flushed from an icy wind
shivers in his tree stand as the sky begins to brighten. He listens
to the noises of the forest: The rush of a nearby river, the cawing
of an obnoxious crow, the scurrying and barking of squirrels, the
constant roar of the morning rush hour traffic and the
``thump-thump-thump'' of a bass on steroids coming from some music
lover's car. Say what? Ivie is hunting within earshot of I-20 and a
major road leading to it. Not exactly the pastoral scene that comes
to mind when the word ``hunt'' comes up. (Mitchell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS. FOR SUNDAY
</P>
