<HEADLINE>
MISSISSIPPI MAN WANTED FOR KILLING IN POLICE CUSTODY 
</HEADLINE>
   (ATTN: Arkansas, Mississippi, Tennessee, Texas)  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By DANE SCHILLER  
 c.1998 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAREDO, Texas _ A man wanted for murder, theft and other charges
who was apprehended by the Mexican police after a daring escape
across the border was in custody Thursday in a Texas jail.
</P>
<P>
   James Edward Tillis was being held in the Webb County Jail here
after Mexican authorities turned him over to a Texas Ranger, a jail
official said.
</P>
<P>
   U.S. authorities were spared what could have been a lengthy
battle to have Tillis extradited when the Mexican government
deported him early Thursday for entering that country illegally.
</P>
<P>
   Tillis, 30, of Lambert, Miss., violated immigration laws by
swimming across the Rio Grande to flee U.S. Border Patrol agents
and entering the country without permission, a federal prosecutor
in Mexico said.
</P>
<P>
   The next step is for prosecutors in Texas, Arkansas and possibly
Tennessee to decide who will be the first to try Tillis, who is
wanted for knifing two people in Arkansas, killing one of them, and
for allegedly tying up a man near Austin, Texas, and stealing his
truck. It was not clear Thursday why the man was being sought in
Tennessee.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a lot of details that need to be worked out,'' Capt.
Billy Williams of the West Helena, Ark., police said. ``We're
mostly waiting.''
</P>
<P>
   Two Mexican policemen arrested Tillis on Wednesday after they
spotted him strolling through a Nuevo Laredo shopping district a
few blocks from the Rio Grande.
</P>
<P>
   Dozens of officers had been searching for Tillis, who doesn't
speak Spanish and was last seen climbing from the river after
fleeing Border Patrol agents who were pursuing him on the U.S. side
of the river.
</P>
<P>
   In an interview at the federal police headquarters in Nuevo
Laredo, Tillis said that he felt remorse for a crime spree that he
said was triggered over personal problems with a former girlfriend.
</P>
<P>
   ``I lost my temper and was caught in a whirlpool of sin,''
Tillis said. ``When that happens, anything can happen.''
</P>
<P>
   Alvin King, 44, of West Helena, was killed Sunday. Brenda Green,
the mother of Tillis' former girlfriend, had her throat slashed and
was treated at a hospital.
</P>
<P>
   A man matching Tillis' description was scene by a Texas state
trooper using a coat hanger to get into a vehicle that had been
reported stolen. The police said Tillis escaped by tying up a man
near Austin and stealing his truck.
</P>
<P>
   He was spotted in Laredo and chased before jumping into the
river and swimming to Mexico. The stolen truck was found in Laredo.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
