<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-XMASDAY25-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    It's not too late to catch your holiday favorites
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Say that your favorite holiday film is 1983's ``A Christmas
Story.'' You know, the one with little Peter Billingsley pining for
a Red Ryder BB gun.
</P>
<P>
   And say, it being Christmas Day and all, you want to watch it.
What do you do? Turn on the television.
</P>
<P>
   TNT is in the midst of a ``Christmas Story'' marathon, airing
the film again and again and again until 8 tonight, when, suddenly,
what in your wondering eyes should appear but ``How the Grinch
Stole Christmas: Special Edition.''
</P>
<P>
   There is a lot of great holiday viewing available today.
Probably too much for any holiday-obsessed couch potato to absorb
it all. What follows is a guide to the best.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  The mother of all Christmas flicks: Zuzu's petals come into
play for the third time this season with NBC's final airing this
year of 1946's ``It's a Wonderful Life'' (8 tonight ).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Something merry and bright: 1942's ``Holiday Inn'' (11:30 a.m.
on AMC ) features the Oscar-winning ``White Christmas'' warbled by
Bing Crosby.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  God bless this one: The most critically acclaimed version of
``A Christmas Carol'' is the 1951 vehicle (2:30 p.m. on AMC )
starring Alastair Sim and airing in glorious black-and-white.
Viewers with younger kids have permission to flip to ``The Muppet
Christmas Carol'' (4 p.m. on Disney ) or to ``Mr. Magoo's Christmas
Carol'' (5 p.m. on PaxNet ).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  It's not just Christmas: ``Harambee Kwanzaa'' (8 p.m. on BET )
explores the African-American holiday.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  That family on the hill: TNN celebrates with ``The Waltons,''
including ``The Best Christmas'' episode at 1 p.m. and 6 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Tunes worth hearing: Great holiday music shows include
``Carols From Atlanta: The 70th Anniversary Morehouse-Spelman
Christmas Carol Concert'' (7 a.m. on WGTV ), ``Jessye Norman: A
Holiday Homecoming'' (8 a.m. on WGTV and 8:30 p.m. on WPBA ),
``Gospel Tabernacle Christmas Special'' (9 a.m. on WATL ),
``Atlanta Symphony: Christmas With Robert Shaw'' (9:30 a.m. on WGTV
) and ``Holiday Music Videos'' (9:30 a.m. on VH1 ).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Visions of sugarplums: ``Christmas at Biltmore Estate'' (11
a.m. on HGTV ) and ``White House Christmas'' (1 p.m. and 6 p.m. on
HGTV ).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Very merry marketing: This year's ``Very Merry Christmas
Parade'' touting everything Disney starts at 10 a.m. on ABC .
</P>
<P>
   Bob Longino writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
