<P>
   CHRISTMAS-GULF (Aboard the USS Belleau Wood, Persian Gulf) _ The
season of peace on earth, good will toward men seems incongruous
with the mission of the thousands of American soldiers, sailors and
aviators massed in a region that has become synonymous with
bloodshed and turmoil. By Colin Nickerson. 1100 words.
</P>
