</P>
<P>
   MULTIPLE-TRANSPLANTS (Boston) _ Teams recover two lungs and a
heart from a single donor and implant them into three patients on
the brink of death. About 100 physicians, surgeons, nurses and
other specialists carry out the logistically complex mission. By
Richard Saltus. 800 words.
</P>
