   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ECONOMY-DATA (Washington) _ Government says Americans earned
more, saved more, and were forced to visit the unemployment office
less often in recent weeks. By Aaron Zitner. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   TOBIN-BOSCI (Boston) -- James Tobin, who resigned abruptly as
chief executive of Biogen, is on the short list of candidates for
the new chief operating officer of Boston Scientific. By Ronald
Rosenberg. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Foxborough, Mass.) -- It isn't just the Patriots
vs. the Jets or Pete Carroll vs. Bill Parcells. Sunday's regular
season finale is a battle of philosophies. By Nick Cafardo.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PARCELLS (Hempstead, N.Y.) _ Bill Parcells says he has put
New England behind him. Maybe he has. But New England certainly
hasn't put Parcells behind it, and the Jets coach addressed that
particular phenomenon before late-morning workout at Hofstra. By
Peter May.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   FBN-TESTAVERDE (Elmont, N.Y.) _ Vinny Testaverde has spent
Christmas the past few years in Baltimore and Cleveland. He makes
his offseason home near Tampa. This year, however, he's home for
Christmas. By Peter May.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
