   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Friday, Dec. 25. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
CLINTON-EVIDENCE (Undated) - While House Majority whip Tom DeLay
urges Senators to visit the highly secretive Judiciary Committee
evidence room, colleague J.D. Hayworth is stirring the same pot by
acting as a source on the mystery evidence for national news media
and calling KFYI at home. In the call to the local radio station,
Hayworth declined to reveal what he had seen in the room, but he
did permit himself to observe that is proved President Clinton is a
``sexual predator.'' Hayworth's actions are disturbing to at least
one member of Congress, who told The Republic that members were
told to keep the mystery evidence private and further that he had
already resolved not to look at it because it had not been
introduced into evidence and because it could taint any appeal
process he might have to be a part of, however remote that
possibility might be. By MIKE MCCLOY. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SHAKESPEARE-MOVIE (Undated) - It is the summer of 1593, and young
Will Shakespeare has a paralyzing bout of writer's block for his
latest play, ``Romeo and Ethel, the Pirate's Daughter.'' That is,
until he meets Gwyneth Paltrow. By BOB FENSTER. Story moved in the
``E'' category. 5 stars. &QL; 
 &QL; 
