<P>
   FOR FRIDAY AMs
</P>
<P>
   Business Day Front Page (coded ``f'' unless otherwise noted): &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Lede story)
</P>
<P>
   ECON-REPORT (Undated) _ U.S. consumers took a late-autumn pause
last month from their recent relatively heavy levels of spending,
as incomes surged and personal savings grew for the first time in
four months. Jobless claims also fell last week to their lowest
level in more than a year. Together with the recent performance of
the stock market, those signs point to continued economic
expansion, economists said. By Edward Wyatt.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Display)
</P>
<P>
   BOMBARDIER (Montreal) _ Bombardier, the Canadian company best
known for making snowmobiles, has become an aggressive
international transportation-equipment giant, with $6.1 billion in
annual revenues. Bombardier also has developed a knack for
enlisting government help, a strategy that often gets it unwanted
attention in Canada and in many foreign countries. By Anthony
DePalma.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo is being sent to NYT photo clients. Graphic is
being sent to NYT graphic clients. Non-subscribers can make
individual purchase by calling (888) 603-1036 or (888) 346-9867.) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Bottom Center)
</P>
<P>
   EURO (Rome) _ Although euro coins and notes will not start
appearing until late 2001, bank accounts, credit-card bills and
phone bills will be denominated in euros in only a few days. For
such uses, the euro is likely to be embraced quickly by the
estimated 35 million Europeans who now use several currencies
daily. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Bottom Right)
</P>
<P>
   PRUDENTIAL-SUIT (Undated) _ Two years after Prudential Insurance
Company of America agreed to compensate millions of policyholders
to end a lawsuit contending that the company's agents engaged in
dishonest sales practices, the program is running months behind
schedule and, across the United States, people are complaining. By
Joseph B. Treaster.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   BIZGLANCE (Undated) _ Digest of the day's financial stories.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
