   LEAD-PAINT-PARKS (Los Angeles) _ After temporarily closing six
city parks because of lead contamination, officials released a list
of 122 that they say probably will be safe for children, as long as
they wash their hands afterward. Just a year ago, city officials
insisted the parks were free of lead paint because the equipment
was being replaced. By Rick Orlov. (Will move in the ``a'' national
and ``n'' California news files.)
