<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-NOTES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SANDERS TO OBTAIN 2ND OPINION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Cowboys cornerback Deion Sanders will have his
sprained left toe examined Tuesday by specialist Dr. Bill Hamilton
in Florida, but Sanders is not optimistic about his iffy status
changing.
</P>
<P>
   Sanders, who has missed five-plus games and is questionable to
play again this season, said he is getting the second opinion at
the urging of Cowboys owner Jerry Jones.
</P>
<P>
   Sanders said he is frustrated about being sidelined during what
he called one of his best seasons, and said he has turned his
health over to the Lord.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know how much it's \Rseeing Hamilton\S going to
help,'' Sanders said. ``He may be able to tell me something more in
depth. But I don't think anything can be said to get me on the
field quicker.''
</P>
<P>
   Sanders has a point, considering that the only option other than
rest is surgery, which would end any chance of him playing in the
playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   Sanders will not play against the Washington Redskins on Sunday
night and is likely to be doubtful for the Cowboys' first-round
playoff game the first weekend in January. However, he has not
given up hope of playing in the playoffs and is eying a return for
a possible second-round game in Atlanta against the Falcons, the
team he began his NFL career with in 1989.
</P>
<P>
   Hamilton, based in New York, has performed surgery on Cowboys
running back Emmitt Smith.
LAFLEUR EXPERIENCES DISCOMFORT
</P>
<P>
   Tight end David LaFleur (sprained knee) practiced yesterday but
complained of discomfort, causing coach Chan Gailey to take a
wait-and-see approach to LaFleur's status for the Redskins game.
</P>
<P>
   LaFleur, who has missed two games, is a key factor in the
Cowboys' power running game. Coaches were hoping to get him back
into the flow before the playoffs. Gailey said it will be a
game-time decision. Playoff tickets available Several thousand
tickets are available for the first-round playoff game. The Cowboys
will play either Tampa Bay, the New York Giants or Arizona at Texas
Stadium. Ticket prices are $52 to $72. Call Ticketmaster at (214)
373-8000 or (972) 579-4800. The Cowboys' ticket office number is
(972) 579-4800.
HE SAID IT
``I can't evaluate the year until the year is over. It's hard to
determine right now how successful a season it's been because we're
still in the middle of it. I'm proud of the fact we won the
division. But for those of us in this locker room, that wasn't the
ultimate goal coming into the year.'' _ Cowboys quarterback Troy
Aikman
</P>
</TEXT>
